[In the previous posting (see Measles - Australia: (QL) alert, RFI
20100210.0463), there were several press reports announcing a measles
alert. Two were from Queensland, one was from Northern Territory
(Darwin). No country of origin was given in the reports of the case
in Queensland, whereas the alert from Darwin mentioned the individual
had arrived in Darwin on a flight coming from Ho Chi Minh City
(HCMC), Viet Nam. In the 2nd newswire in this current posting, there
is mention that the case in Queensland is in a French national. It
is still unclear if this French national is the same individual who
reportedly arrived in Darwin from Viet Nam. (From the dates
mentioned, it is highly likely that the alerts are referring to the
same individual). It is likely that passengers on the same flight
(or flights -- HCMC to Darwin, Darwin to Sydney) could have been
infected and there is risk that measles infection could be
transmitted elsewhere in Australia. Information on the route of entry
of the measles virus-infected tourist is relevant and would be
welcomed. It is surprising that this information has not been
disseminated so far.

Maps of Queensland showing the location of Airlie Beach and the
Whitsundays can be accessed at
<http://www.about-australia.com/maps/queensland/> and the
HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map at
<http://healthmap.org/r/0172>. - Mods.CP/MPP]
